## Verdict: BLOCK

### 1. [high] AC-050a’s 0.5.x verb-reroute check is not implemented
Refs: [dev/acceptance.md](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/dev/acceptance.md:794), [dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/dev/plans/0.6.0-implementation.md:941), [scripts/security/ast_scan.py](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/scripts/security/ast_scan.py:31), [dev/plans/runs/12-S-security-fixtures-output.json](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/dev/plans/runs/12-S-security-fixtures-output.json:93)

`V05_VERBS` is empty, so the scanner’s Rust/Python/TS “0.5.x verb re-route stub” branches never fire. That leaves one explicit AC-050a clause unenforced: “zero re-route stubs from 0.5.x verb names.” The closure artifact already documents this as a no-op, so this is not just missing test coverage; it is missing enforcement.

### 2. [medium] The Rust scanner does not actually exclude block comments/docs, and the self-test does not cover that requirement
Refs: [dev/acceptance.md](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/dev/acceptance.md:798), [scripts/security/ast_scan.py](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/scripts/security/ast_scan.py:77), [scripts/tests/test_ast_scan.sh](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/scripts/tests/test_ast_scan.sh:13), [scripts/tests/fixtures/ast-shim/rust/dirty/legacy_admin.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/scripts/tests/fixtures/ast-shim/rust/dirty/legacy_admin.rs:1)

`scan_rust()` only skips lines whose trimmed text starts with `//`. It does not skip `/* ... */` / `/** ... */` bodies, even though AC-050a explicitly says comments and docs are excluded. The Rust self-test also misses the crate-root `#![allow(deprecated)]` rule: the negative fixture places that attribute in `legacy_admin.rs`, but the scanner only checks `lib.rs` / `main.rs`, so the test passes on the filename/prefix violations without exercising the crate-root-specific branch.

### 3. [high] The aggregate AC-036/037 gate is still not demonstrated as a hard CI gate
Refs: [scripts/agent-security.sh](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/scripts/agent-security.sh:20), [dev/plans/runs/12-S-security-fixtures-output.json](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/dev/plans/runs/12-S-security-fixtures-output.json:68), [scripts/bootstrap.sh](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/scripts/bootstrap.sh:43)

`agent-security.sh` treats rc=2 as non-fatal unless `STRICT=1`, and the closure artifact records a passing aggregate run with two blockers. I found no in-repo test or workflow wiring that proves `STRICT=1` is what CI will use. So real violations fail loudly, but the blocker path for AC-036/037 is still policy-by-convention, not a demonstrated gate.

On the bootstrap side, the Linux/macOS gating is directionally correct: current GitHub docs say `ubuntu-latest` is Ubuntu 24.04 and Linux hosted runners have passwordless `sudo`, so `sudo apt-get install strace` is plausible there. But GitHub’s runner customization docs explicitly recommend `sudo apt-get update` before install, and this script omits that, so even the proposed CI remediation is not fully hardened. Sources: https://docs.github.com/en/actions/reference/runners/github-hosted-runners and https://docs.github.com/en/actions/how-tos/manage-runners/github-hosted-runners/customize-runners

**Addressed**
- The shipped dirty AST fixtures for Rust, Python, and TS are all flagged when run directly.
- The AC-050c moved-in-file case is handled correctly: same-name reappearance in the same file cancels the removal.

**What passed on inspection**
- AC-050c’s implementation distinguishes same-file moves from true removals via same-path/same-name cancellation in [scripts/security/check_removal_changelog.py](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/scripts/security/check_removal_changelog.py:123), and the shipped fixture covers that path.
- AC-038 is not just “no `SQLITE_ERROR`”: the test also checks result-set parity via `parity_failures` in [fts5_injection_safety.rs](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/fts5_injection_safety.rs:123). It covers 100 queries and includes `"`, `*`, `^`, `NEAR`, `AND`, and `OR`.
- The CHANGELOG stub is minimally viable for AC-050c because it already provides `## [Unreleased]` and `### Removed` in [CHANGELOG.md](/tmp/fdb-12-S-security-fixtures-20260517T195735Z/CHANGELOG.md:1).

**Reviewer process notes**
- Read everything requested except `dev/plans/prompts/12-S-security-fixtures.md`; that file is not present in this checkout.
- Executed the three dirty AST fixtures and the moved-in-file removal fixture directly.
- Could not create scratch fixtures or run the cargo-backed gates end-to-end in this sandbox because the filesystem is read-only; `cargo test` under `agent-security.sh` fails here on target-dir writes, so the strict blocker path was assessed from code plus current GitHub-hosted runner docs rather than a clean end-to-end CI-style run.
